---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { Callie, Roaster } from "@callies-universe/core";
import { SHOWS } from "../config/sites.js";
const live = SHOWS.filter((s) => s.status === "live").length;
const total = SHOWS.length;
// Callie's whole vocabulary: she only reacts. A few of her expressive states.
const reactions = ["delighted", "savage", "celebrating", "cooking", "comfort", "curious"];
const STAR = "polygon(50% 0,59% 18%,78% 8%,75% 30%,97% 28%,82% 46%,100% 60%,78% 64%,86% 88%,63% 78%,55% 100%,44% 79%,22% 90%,28% 66%,4% 64%,22% 48%,2% 32%,24% 30%,20% 8%,40% 18%)";
---
<Base title="About Callie" description="Who Callie is: the cat who runs the studio, but never roasts you.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:18px;">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="position:relative;display:inline-grid;place-items:center;margin:0 auto 4px;">
        <span class="ink" aria-hidden="true" style={`position:absolute;inset:-20px;background:var(--accent-bright);clip-path:${STAR};`}></span>
        <div style="position:relative;"><Callie state="celebrating" size={150} ink /></div>
      </div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Meet the host</p>
      <h1 class="title-stroke">Meet <span class="hl"><span class="hl__mark"></span><span class="hl__tx">Callie</span></span>.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Callie loves you way too much to roast you, so she hired comedians who don't.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:14px;padding-bottom:24px;">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Why there's a cat</h2>
      <p>Callie runs the studio. It's literally her universe. The catch: she's a calico with a heart three sizes too big. She'd start a roast and apologize halfway through. So she did the next best thing: she hired a cast of comedians who <em>won't</em> apologize, gave them a stage, and pulled up a chair in the corner to watch. The comedians bring the heat. Callie's just there, losing it, on your side the whole time.</p>

      <h2>She never says a word</h2>
      <p>Callie has never spoken. Nobody's sure she can. She doesn't need to. Her whole job is to feel it <em>with</em> you, and her face says everything.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section band" style="background:var(--accent-700);padding:46px 0;">
    <span class="band__dots halftone"></span>
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <p class="eyebrow" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.82);">Her whole vocabulary</p>
      <h2 style="color:#fff;font-size:30px;margin:6px 0 26px;text-shadow:3px 3px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.22);">No words. Just reactions.</h2>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:16px;justify-content:center;">
        {reactions.map((s) => (
          <div style="background:#fff;border:var(--ink-outline);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);corner-shape:var(--corner-card);box-shadow:var(--shadow-sticker-md);padding:6px;">
            <Callie state={s} size={86} ink />
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>One studio, many shows</h2>
      <p>Every “Roast My ___” show shares the same universe: the same host, the same cast of comedians, the same craft. {live} of {total} shows are live; the rest are warming up in the green room. Find a comic you love in one show and you'll find them in the next.</p>

      <h2>Clever, never cruel</h2>
      <p>The comedy always aims at the <em>thing</em> (the car, the texts, the fit), never at you. Callie is the proof: she'd never let it get mean. It's a roast of your stuff, with a cat who's firmly on your team.</p>

      <p style="margin-top:6px;color:color-mix(in srgb,var(--ink) 55%,transparent);font-size:15px;">Callie and every comedian are original fictional characters we created and own, not impersonations of anyone real. Deep cut: her full name is Calliope. Yes, like the muse. No, she won't talk about it.</p>

      <div style="display:flex;gap:14px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:30px;">
        <a class="btn" href="/characters">Meet the cast →</a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/#shows">See the shows</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
